Land Rover Discovery 2 - LAND ROVER - The best 4x4 by far!! Luxury SUV 119k+ miles. RUST FREE SOUTH CAROLINA TRUCK!!

This vehicle is loaded with features and options: 

Interior:

Sumptuous leather seating with 8-way pwr driver and passenger seat, 60/40 split folding rear seat-inc: armrest w/cup holder, headrests, optional full winter driving package including heated front seats, heated mirrors, and rear window defroster, Pwr windows-inc: front one-touch down feature, retained accessory pwr, backlit controls, Steering wheel mounted audio controls, Burled wood trim, Alcantara door trim, dual zone climate control, two sunroofs, 10 speaker 6 disc cd changer cassette stereo with subwoofer, Optional Factory Land Rover rubber front floor mats, cargo cover with storage bins.

Safety and Security:

Security alarm system-inc: perimeter protection, engine immobilizer, Homelink programmable garage door opener, factory front and rear fog lights.

Powertrain: 4.0L 188 HP V8 with 250 Ft-lbs Torque - Aluminum block and heads, FULL TIME 4x4 with traction control (Land Rover was the first with this), factory tow hitch rated for 7000 lbs, and factory hill descent control, cruise control and factory hill descent control, factory 130 amp alternator.

This truck was a North/South Carolina truck for its entire history so has never been exposed to road salt and has zero rust on the underbody and I immediately coated it with eastwood internal frame coating inside and out upon our purchase. (almost all northern trucks have frame rust issues from years on salted roads). Overall the truck is in excellent condition - rides and drives smooth. 

I am a Land Rover enthusiast and currently have 4 in the family - Mine, Wifes, Off-road truck, and daughters. This one I built for my daughter to drive to college 5 hours away, so I pre-emptively replaced everything I thought could possibly go wrong. This includes the following: Starter, battery, head gaskets, intake manifold gaskets, blower fan, water pump, ignition coils, spark plug wires, all cooling system hoses, thermostat, brake master cylinder, crank position sensor, headliner, power steering pump, door lock motors, transmission fluid (synthetic), and shifter boots . Front driveshaft is upgraded with grease fittings at both ends. 

Beautiful Black paint in excellent condition! 

Check engine light is NOT ON - Does NOT run hot, does NOT overheat, does NOT leak oil. Everything works perfectly! Truck is ready to drive!

To see why Land Rover is the best 4x4 by far - watch this video: 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d9pP4Jnk6H4 and this one: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IIU0rnsfdQ4

Title: clean
Description:
Just purchased this beautiful Deep Black Pearl, 6MT 2016 Golf R from sunny Georgia a few months ago b/c I thought my next duty assignment was going to be Alaska. Turns out things changed and now I'll be moving to England at the end of July so figured I'd try to find a good home for the car in the U.S. and I'll pick something up when I get overseas. Not a big deal if it doesn't sell as this would also make a great car for the U.K.

The car arrived to me with 18,520 miles on the clock via covered transport from it's original owner (he purchased it brand new for $36,555). The car currently sits, in my garage, under a car cover, with 18,725 miles. Such a shame because in the few miles I've put on this bad boy I can honestly say it's the BEST all-around driver I've ever owned. Comfort, speed, handling, technology, looks... it truly has it all. But you guys already know that. I'm coming from 3 MKIV R32s, a MKV R32, B6 and B8 S4's and an E46 M3... this car stands out even among all of those.

The car is in immaculate condition as you can imagine an 18k car would be. The paint shines bright with no significant dings, dents, or scratches. The interior looks and smells absolutely new, only monster mats have ever been used, which has kept the carpet looking fresh. Brand new tires. Can eat off of the engine, zero mechanical issues ever. I purchased a $180 Pre-Purchase Inspection from VW in Marietta, GA which shows a perfectly clean bill of health, happy to send it to whoever is interested. 2 sets of keys, all books, maintenance documents, and original window sticker included. No accidents, no mechanical problems, no issues what-so-ever. Has never seen rain or snow and has never been daily driven (the original owner and myself both have other daily drivers). Garage queen here.

Some details about the car:
-Expel custom cut clear bra full front bumper, mirror caps, 1/4 hood and 1/4 fenders ($800)
-Suntek Carbon Series Tint ($450 - keeps the interior nice and cool)
-Diesel Geek Short Shifter ($190 - amazing, rifle bolt action feel)
-APR Stage I ECU Upgrade ($800)
-VW Golf Monster Mats ($105)
-Titan Black Leather Interior
-Roadside Assistance Kit ($85)
-18" Alloy wheels w/ performance summer tires

So the car was $36,555 new, plus the tasteful modifications puts the original price up to just shy of $40k. Kelly Blue book has the Private Party Value at $32k. Car is located in San Antonio, TX so please feel free to arrange to come and test drive it. I am also willing to ship the car. Please feel free to email me with any questions. The car is literally parked in the garage, under a cover, waiting for someone to give her a good home. Title in hand, ready to go. Cheers - Anthony

Title: rebuilt
Description:
To check the options this vehicle comes equipped with click on the options tab on the listing on our page (www.buyrightautocenter.com). If you're interested in seeing the vehicle's history report--send us a message and we would gladly oblige. The Land Rover Range Rover has salvage history due to a minor left-side collision and we replaced the 2 left doors; also, the title on the vehicle has "non actual mileage" due to not being able to read the mileage at the auction (no battery). The vehicle's exterior/interior is in mint condition and runs great.

CONTACT
If you have any questions, requests and/or would like to set up an appointment to inspect the vehicle -- you can send a message through the method provided where this listing appears or call/text (for quick replies) (347) 467-0227.

ABOUT US
We specialize (but not limited to) in buying quality salvage title vehicles and saving our customers over 25% on what they would be paying purchasing the same vehicle with clear title. The listed price is the price of the vehicle (no hidden fees--taxes and registration not included--New York buyers add 8.75% tax and $200 registration). We inspect/use our vehicles and wouldn't sell a vehicle to a potential customer knowing it wasn't up to par with our high standards. All of our vehicles comes with a 30-day engine and transmission warranty. If you're a potential long distance buyer who's unable to inspect the vehicle at our lot, we offer a 5-days (from when vehicle is received) return policy; if buyer is not 100% satisfied with their purchase (the vehicle wasn't as described), they could return the vehicle in the conditions it was received (no extra costs--buyer is responsible for shipping). Most of our vehicles are sold before they hit our lot (through inner network) but we're working on building new relationships and a reputation with the public. You can check us out at www.buyrightautocenter.com.

Title: clean
Description:
The car has approximately 37,000 miles as of June of 2018.

The car has never been launched, raced, tracked, autocrossed or otherwise abused in any way.

I am the third owner, and know the history of the previous two owners. All owners, including myself, are mature adult professionals. The car was not driven regularly until I purchased it late in 2014. The first owner installed most of the modifications listed below when he purchased it, and sold it after a couple of months of ownership with approximately 1,000 miles. The second owner put approximately 5,500 miles on the car in the four years he owned it. Since I purchased the car, I have used it almost exclusively to drive to and from work. All owners, including myself, were meticulous about maintenance and upkeep. The car has always been garage kept, and has been detailed regularly. Until I purchased it, it had never been driven in rain or snow.

The car has performed flawlessly and hasn't had so much of a hiccup or warranty issue. Aside from a few marks in the clear bra, a couple of chips and minor curb rash on a couple of wheels, and a couple of door dings, both the the interior and exterior are in excellent condition and there isn't so much of a swirl mark on the paint. The car has never been eaten in or smoked in, and has never transported any pets.

The car is currently covered by a bumper-to-bumper extended warranty that I purchased through my reputable credit union. The warranty covered the car from 5 years from the date of purchase, or until the car reaches 100,000 miles, whichever occurs first. I did extensive research on the extended warranty, and found that this company actually pays claims with no hassle (compared to lots of other extended warranties that are full of loopholes and exclusions). The warranty is transferable for a small fee, which I will cover if someone wants to purchase the remainder of the warranty for $650 (otherwise I can get a pro-rated refund since I haven't used it to date).

All maintenance is up to date, and the car has a new battery, new spark plugs and a fresh alignment.

Modifications on car when I purchased:
- Buschur Crossflow catback exhaust
- Buschur UICP (brushed)
- Buschur LICP (brushed)
- Buschur Intake and Air Filter Kit (brushed)
- Buschur Tune: 300 awhp / 277 awtq @ 21 psi
- Prosport boost gauge
- AMS FMIC w/ stencil
- Swift Springs with street-performance alignment
- PIAA Xtreme White DRL bulbs (DRLs currently disabled via pulled fuse)
- Works Underhood Shift Bushings
- Clear Bra on front bumper, fenders hood, side skirts and lower rear portion of rear doors
- Electronic Boost Controller (not installed, and has never been used)
- RallyArmor mud flaps

Modifcations I have added:
- TWM Full-Replacement Cage and Short Shifter
- Titanium custom shift knob
- Interior Door Panels (vinyl/leather-like) from Evo X MR

Description:
This Forester is mechanically sound, runs great, drives great, handles amazingly in the winter, and has been regularly serviced by the excellent independent Subaru repair shop, Wrenchrite Automotive, in Branford, CT. They have recently gone through the entire vehicle. Of note, most Subarus at some point need the head gaskets replaced. Wrenchrite did a complete head gasket job on this vehicle at 127,000 miles, using longer lasting head gaskets than stock, and including replacing the timing belt and water pump. With that already taken care of, along with other work listed below, this Forester is set up to keep going for a long time. 

Here is a list of major repairs done by Wrenchrite (I can provide all receipts):

-April 2018, $804.00: New radiator, hoses, clamps, coolant. Left inner tie rod rack and boot, alignment.

-145,289 miles, $443.48: New harmonic balancer, belt, & drive belts

-143, 326 miles, $1,325.00: Complete rear brake job including new hardware and cylinders. New left and right rear struts. New left and right inner tie rods.

-127,712 miles, $3750.00: Complete head gasket job, new cam/crank seals, valve cover gaskets, spark plugs, drive bels, thermostat, & all timing parts replaced including water pump.  New left rear wheel bearing. U-joint bolt and driveshaft replacement. New left axle, seals and O-rings both sides, sway bar links and bushings: front and rear, service transmission, & new O2 sensor.
_________

Additionally, oil has been changed a few hundred miles ago, and I installed new front brake pads.

Intended to compete on a level playing field with German compact and mid-size sport sedans, as well as a variety of roughly comparable Japanese and American models, the Infiniti G37 Sedan matches smart appearance, bold performance and crisp responsive handling in four trim levels and offers both rear-wheel-drive and all-wheel-drive configurations. Equipped with the same 3.7-liter V6 found in the 370Z Coupe, the G37 Sedan enhances its credentials as a true enthusiast vehicle, inside and out. Although domestics models, including the Cadillac CTS and Lincoln MKZ, or Japanese counterparts, including the Acura TL and Lexus ES 350, are prime targets of opportunity, Infiniti is most intent on having the G37 sedan score biggest with folks who are also shopping the Audi A4, BMW 3 Series and Mercedes-Benz C-Class.

You'll Like This Car If...
Those who prefer a bit more emotional approach to a feature-rich entry-luxury sport sedan should find happiness with virtually any iteration of the Infiniti G37, but particularly one of the Sport-fortified variants.


What's New for 2010
For 2010, the G37 receives a new grille, front fascia (Base and Sport) and new 17-inch wheels. An eight-way power passenger seat is now standard, as are one-touch up/down rear windows. The Journey trim gains a backup camera, heated seats and heated outside mirrors, while the available navigation system now offers Spanish language support for voice commands and displays. Last year's Active Steering option is no longer available.

Driving It
Driving Impressions
Derived from a long-wheelbase version of Nissan's latest FM (Front Mid-ship) platform, the G37 possesses sparkling performance credentials that only improve when fortified with the Sport Package goodies. Driven normally, this scintillating sedan coddles, comforts and entertains. Drive it enthusiastically, and the G37 satisfies like few competitors can. Its lusty V6 pulls strongly on demand, whether backed by the seven-speed automatic or six-speed manual transmission. The finely-tuned suspension delivers impressively balanced ride and handling and the powerful anti-lock brakes stop with authority. All variants benefit from a driver-selectable Vehicle Dynamic Control (VDC) system that lets you explore an ample portion of the car's ultimate potential before the system swings into action. Those willing to forego a bit of at-the-limit edge for the all-season security of all-wheel drive should consider a G37x.

Favorite Features
Power Front Seats 
Amazingly comfortable and supportive, even the base G37's front seats boast eight-way power adjustment for the driver and passenger, plus manually adjustable lumbar supports. The Sport 6MT seats include power activation for the thigh, lumbar and side bolsters. 

Hard Drive Based Navigation 
This all-in-one information center not only offers voice-activated navigation, it includes XM NavTraffic and NavWeather updates, Zagat restaurant guide, steaming Bluetooth for audio, 9.3-gigabyte music box storage and DVD playback capability.

Vehicle Details

Interior
Superbly-formed power front seats wrapped in leather and set off by aluminum accent trim textured to resemble traditional Japanese handmade paper add a unique flavor to the G37's cabin styling. Its cockpit-like ambiance may strike some as a bit busy, but the controls are logically arrayed and soothing white on black main gauges are quite legible. Not so much for the center stack - with or without optional navigation - where display legibility tends to come or go based upon the amount of reflecting sunlight. Rear passengers will find the G37 Sedan's rear bench seat belted for three but contoured for two average-sized adults at best.

Exterior
Well-tailored sheetmetal effectively complements the 2010 Infiniti G37 Sedan's sporting character, melding crisp lines and sensual contours into a tasteful yet visually distinctive styling statement. Complementing the basic shape are an eye-catching grille treatment with four sculpted bars that twist from center to edge like traditional Japanese sword blades, flush-fit L-shaped headlights and taillights that flow around the fenders front and rear and standard 225/55 V-rated tires on 17-inch alloy wheels. The top-line G37S Sport 6MT and G37x models have W-rated 225/50 front and 245/45 rear tires on 18-inch alloy rims.

Notable Standard Equipment
Exceptionally well appointed, even the base G37 Sedan offers leather upholstery, a full range of power assists - including dual eight-way power front seats - steering wheel-mounted supplemental audio and cruise controls, Intelligent Key remote entry and push button start, six-speaker AM/FM/MP3-capable audio with six-disc changer and auxiliary input, automatic air conditioning and high-intensity discharge (HID) bi-xenon headlights. The Journey, G37x and G37S Sport 6MT bring Infiniti's Rearview Monitor, Bluetooth hand-free phone connectivity, heated outside mirrors, a USB connection port and other detail upgrades. Standard safety features on all include front, front-side and side-curtain airbags, active front-seat head restraints, Vehicle Dynamic Control (VDC) with stability and traction control and anti-lock brakes (ABS) with Brake Assist (BA) and Electronic Brake force Distribution (EBD).

Notable Optional Equipment
The G37 offers multiple upgrade packages and several individual extras, although only for the Journey, G37x or G37 Sport 6MT models. Key groups include the Premium Package (moonroof, Bose audio system, power tilt and telescoping steering column, and more), Sport Package (sport steering wheel and seats, four-piston sport brakes unique front fascia and side sills, 18-inch wheels and tires, limited-slip differential and magnesium paddle shifters with the automatic), Technology Package (Intelligent Cruise Control, adaptive front lighting and more) and the Navigation Package (voice-activation, real-time XM NavTraffic, RearView Monitor, Lane Guidance and a 9.3GB Music Box hard drive). Also available are Maple accent interior trim, ambient interior accent lighting and a rear spoiler.

Under the Hood
The G37's stellar V6 is the latest iteration of Nissan's renowned VQ35-series engine. This all-aluminum 3.7-liter is loaded with design elements that help reduce internal friction and increase total performance, including continuously variable timing on both the intake and exhaust valves. It delivers a stout 328 horsepower and 269 pound-feet of torque, is matched with either a seven-speed automatic (G37, G37 Journey or G37x) or close-ratio six-speed manual transmission (G37S Sport 6MT) and returns slightly above-average fuel economy numbers. On a G37 fitted with the Sport Package, the automatic also features finger-friendly shifter paddles mounted on the steering column and ideally positioned for quick gear changes. 

3.7-liter V6 
328 horsepower @ 7000 rpm 
269 lb.-ft. of torque @ 5200 rpm 
EPA city/highway fuel economy: 17/25 (manual), 19/27 (automatic), 18/25 (AWD, automatic)

Pricing Notes
The Manufacturer's Suggested Retail Price (MSRP) on the Infiniti G37 line runs from around $34,000 for a base G37 model to about $37,000 for an all-wheel- drive G37x. Those figures make it a rather attractive choice when compared to most of its foes, particularly those with a German pedigree where buying similar horsepower and features will end up costing considerably more. The G37's advantage gets a bit less well-defined when it comes to residual values. All models retain a solid percentage of their original cost over time. However, while the G37 fares better in that department than the Lincoln MXZ, Mercedes-Benz C-Class, Cadillac CTS and Audi A4, it falls just short of the projected residual values held by the Acura TL and far short of the BMW 3 Series and Lexus ES 350.

You'll Like This Car If...
The 2013 E-Class may be the most diverse mid-size luxury car line on the planet. Standard and available features allow custom tailoring to suit each owner's needs, while the E-Class' numerous engine and body style choices have no rival. 

You May Not Like This Car If...
You can certainly find many of the E-Class' features in less-expensive sedans from Cadillac, Infiniti and Lexus. Hard-core driving enthusiasts will probably find the BMW 5 Series delivers a more spirited ride than the E-Class. 

What's New for 2013
The 2013 E-Class Coupe and Cabriolet gain mbrace2 telematics, electromechanical steering and heated front seats. The E400 Hybrid Sport Sedan debuts with a 305-horsepower V6 engine mated to a 27-horsepower electric motor. 

Driving It
Driving Impressions
Despite the vast array of engines offered in the 2013 Mercedes-Benz E-Class, there will always be faster cars on the road - perhaps some of them not a lot faster. However, few can boast the same blend of comfort, luxury and performance. With individual shock absorbers constantly adjusting to road-surface changes and driver demands, the car is both firm and responsive through tight bends and smooth on the highway. Its suspension inspires confidence and the steering is reasonably informative. All this helps make the E-Class a remarkably enjoyable and comfortable vehicle to drive. Those seeking ultimate fuel economy can choose between a clean diesel and hybrid powertrain option. If you'd like to step out closer to the edge, the E63 AMG brings an upgraded engine, suspension and transmission to bear with giggle-inducing speed and precision. The 2013 E63 AMG is available as either a Sedan or Wagon. 

Favorite Features
DISTRONIC PLUS SAFETY PACKAGE 
It's tough to get excited about safety features, but the Distronic Plus Safety Package's features are truly special. The Pre-Safe Brake system uses radar to warn the driver of imminent collision and even applies the brakes to minimize impact. 

SPORT PACKAGE 
Ok, so the Sport Package only shows outwardly with bigger wheels and comes with a swanky contrasting interior. You should buy it for the stiffened (and lowered) suspension, which properly livens up the car's handling. 

Vehicle Details
Interior
Every 2013 Mercedes-Benz E-Class comes loaded with standard equipment, providing comfort and convenience that's fully expected from the brand. From burled walnut interior trim accents to 14-way power seats with memory settings to the premium audio system and "mbrace2" navigation system, the E-Class doesn't leave much room for options (though there are some). Front head- and legroom is very good on all models. The rear seats, however, can be a bit cramped in the Coupe and Cabriolet but are very nice in the Sedan and Wagon. Luggage space is impressive across the line, even in the Cabriolet, which has ample usable trunk space.

Exterior
Combining elements of 1950s sedans and coupes with muscular rear fenders and its signature front-end design, the 2013 Mercedes-Benz E-Class is both distinctive and recognizably Mercedes. The Coupe's lack of a B-pillar gives it a smooth look and an air of class. The Cabriolet shares the Coupe's modified grille and boasts an elegant soft top that blends nicely into its sharp bodylines with a classic look. The Wagon is an unsung hero. From some vantage points, its roofline appears to carry a descending curve from front to back, while from other spots it almost seems to be a straight line to an expansive rear cargo area.

Notable Standard Equipment
All 2013 E-Class models come with an impressive list of standard features. Electronic Brake Assist is standard across the line, as is the 7-speed transmission with paddle shifters fitted to the new multifunction steering wheel. Other standard equipment includes mbrace2 telematics, an 8-speaker 6-disc CD/DVD system, a 7-inch LCD display and a plethora of comfort and convenience features. Safety features include a full array of airbags plus the LATCH (lower anchors and tethers for children) system. Electronic stability control, long a standard on most Mercedes-Benz cars, is now required by the government to be fitted on all 2013 models.

Notable Optional Equipment
Options of note on the 2013 Mercedes-Benz E-Class models include Sport and Luxury Design Packages, the Distronic Plus Package with Pre-Safe Braking and Parktronic parking assist and Premium Packages offering Bluetooth connectivity, iPod/MP3 capability, HD radio and more. For the Sedan and Wagon, leather upholstery is optional and, on all models, the seating is available with heating, ventilation and even massage functions for the driver. Available assistance systems include the Lane Keeping Assist (in both passive and active forms) and Blind Spot Assist.

Under the Hood
For 2013, the Mercedes-Benz E-Class has four engine choices and one hybrid gasoline/electric unit. Gasoline engines include the 210-horsepower, turbocharged 3.0-liter V6 BlueTEC diesel; a 302-horsepower, 3.5-liter V6 in E350 variants; a 402-horsepower, 4.6-liter V8 for the E550 cars and the monster 518-horsepower, 5.5-liter V8 in the E63 AMG sedan and wagon. All E-Class engines run through a 7-speed automatic transmission with optional manual paddle shifting. The 4Matic all-wheel-drive system is available with either the 3.5-liter V6 or the 4.6-liter V8. The E63 AMG cars are equipped with the tuner's Speedshift transmission with Race Start and rev matching.

Description:
Please read the entire description. Yes this Corvette was photographed extensively for a Corvette blog as a beautiful example of the 1986 Convertible. Miss the rumble of a V8?
-	Air Conditioning
-	New Alpine Bluetooth Stereo and speaker system
-	Manual Top (replaced recently)
-	Power Windows
-	Power Seats
-	Tilt /Tele Wheel
-	Antilock Brakes
-	AM/FM Radio
-	Radial Tires
-	Cruise Control
-	Power Locks
-	Power Steering
-	Traction Control
-	Leather Interior

I am the second owner since 1990. 
A yellow convertible was the pace car for the 1986 Indianapolis 500 race. This marked the return of the convertible body style, absent from the Corvette lineup since 1975. All 7,315 1986 convertible Corvettes (all exterior colors) had "Indy 500 Pace Car" console identification. 

This loaded Corvette is finished in Bright Red with the Torch Red interior. It has 64k original miles. It is equipped with the 5.7-liter V8 with Tuned Port Induction. It also has a (4+3 seven speed) 4-speed manual transmission with overdrive. The overdrive was just recently completely serviced and works as it should. It is also equipped with the radiator cooling boost fan, completely digital dash and a rare optional engine oil cooler. 

The engine has been completely removed and rebuilt by Meyers Motors with many HP adding modifications. (I have the work order document.) But to the eye, the engine appears completely stock. The looks are deceiving because the Vette now puts out over 400 HP! Less than 1000 miles have been put on this rebuilt engine! Many parts upgraded or replaced.

Air conditioning, power windows and locks and a brand new Bluetooth Alpine sound system are some of the features that make this a great ride. This Corvette has the beautiful real Rosewood accents on the complete dash and shift console and door panels. Other equipment includes power antenna, Dual electronic control sport mirrors, ABS anti-lock brakes a six-way power seat and A.R.E. aluminum wheels. The Corvette is mint inside and out. Always garaged.

The Corvette is known as the only true American sports car and this is a fine example. You would be hard pressed to find a nicer 1986 Convertible Corvette. The car is located in Windsor CT off I-91. The price is extremely reasonable and firm.

Title: clean
Description:
Subaru Legacy 2001. Green 4-door sedan. I'm the second owner & bought from an elderly woman in California in 2007 with <10K miles on it. I primarily bike so the majority of the last 11 years I drove the car 1-2x/month. Well-maintained and all records included. It has spent the majority of its time either in the dry climate of California or in covered parking. Selling now since parking is expensive in Manhattan.

Amazing dependable car. All Wheel Drive (AWD) - great in the snow. 3-4 sets of skis fit in the car with a fold-down middle section of the back seat. Highly recommend Subarus - they often last 200K-300K miles. Odometer now is ~62,000 (original). Super low mileage for any used car. Perfect for students or commuters.

Features: Brand-new belts (timing, drive) & spark plugs/wires installed in 2016 with full 60K mile tuneup, gray interior no tears or rips, NO accidents, tape cassette player (retro - likely the last year Subarus had cassette players). Cruise control. A/C. Heat. All-season tires. Power steering. ABS. Automatic headlights. Power locks/windows. Intermittent setting windshield wipers. Rear defrost. Air bags. Child safety locks. Fits 5 people comfortably. Trunk fits two large suitcases easily.

Wear: small rack & pinion leak - I top up the power steering fluid about once a year, small dents/scratches/peeling trim from over the years, lime drips crusting on roof/window from a garage - it's coming off but could likely remove it faster with a safe solvent. 

Payment: Cash preferred or cashier's check (will meet at issuing bank), no online payment. Include name & number when contact or I will not respond. Email or text to set up time to see the car. Thanks!

If this post is up then the car is still AVAILABLE!

This post is for a 1950 Oldsmobile Eighty-Eight two door Deluxe Hardtop. 

The engine is a 1962 Oldsmobile 394 cubic inch with 9.5 compression pistons, an Edelbrock Carburetor with Phenolic heat spacer, and Petronis Electronic ignition ending with dual exhaust. 

The transmission is a turbo 400 built by Ross Racing Engines to fit a 394 Oldsmobile Engine.

The front & rear suspension is original type lever shocks. The brakes are drum brakes with power booster and dual master cylinder. It has power steering, electric wipers with a 12-volt system, 3" wide white wall radial tires with 1956 Deluxe Spinner Hub Caps. Inside the car is air conditioning. The car has a radio delete on the dash but under the seat is a hidden stereo that plays FM/AM as well as having an input for a flash drive to play MP3s. It is currently loaded with oldies music from the 40s - 60s. 

The original VIN plate was missing and it now has a Kansas ID number that was obtained through a quiet title action. 

The car drives nice and rides nice. 

The transmission needs a switch for the kick-down for the turbo 400 and the horn does not work. 

The car is black and the body and frame are straight. 

The interior is original with carpet and front seat belts. 

The odometer shows 25,378.

All chrome and stainless trim is excellent.

Up for sale is a 2014 Range Rover Sport SE finished in Santorini Black with an Ebony leather interior. This example has 60,500 miles and is in excellent condition. Powered by a supercharged 3.0L V6, the Range Rover Sport makes 340 horsepower and 332 pound feet of torque. Power is sent to all four wheels through a ZF 8 speed automatic transmission. This Range Rover Sport is a well-optioned example featuring Dark Grey Oak Wood Trim throughout the interior, the Extra Duty package, Climate Comfort and Visibility packages, and a full sliding panoramic sunroof. An 8 inch touch-screen interface with on and off-road navigation, keyless entry, heated front and rear seats, and 14-way adjustable seats are other notable options. Like all Range Rover's, this Sport is set up for off-road and all-weather conditions with an air suspension system that has auto-leveling technology. Additionally, the added Extra Duty package adds Terrain Response, Adaptive Dynamics, and an enhanced transfer case. Aesthetically, this Range Rover Sport is in incredible shape. There are no major scratches, scuffs, or dents to the exterior, and the interior leather shows little wear. Santorini Black is a beautiful metallic color with a slight silver flake throughout the finish. Overall, it will be difficult to find another 2014 Range Rover Sport in this condition. A well-spec'd example, this Sport makes for the perfect luxury SUV.

While Mercedes-Benz is mostly associated with providing high-priced cars to the rich and ultra-rich, the company also has a series of coupes and sedans built to the same high-quality standards but wearing a 5-digit price tag. Offering younger buyers a way into the Mercedes-Benz fold is the C250, a turbocharged 4-cylinder model with a sub-$40,000 price tag. With the C250, Mercedes hopes that first-time buyers will remain loyal as their ages and incomes rise. But the C-Class isn't all about price, with a number of enticing upscale models including the fire-breathing V8-powered C63 AMG. 


You'll Like This Car If...
If you're shopping a loaded Chrysler 300 or Nissan Maxima, it's not a far leap to land in an equally well-equipped 2013 Mercedes-Benz C-Class. And, when it comes time to move to a bigger Benz, the C-Class promises a good return on your investment.


What's New for 2013
New for 2013 is the C300 4Matic's 3.5-liter direct-injection V6 that bumps output to 248 horsepower. A fuel-saving ECO start/stop feature is added to the C350 and C300 4Matic, while Distronic Plus becomes a stand-alone option. Mbrace2 internet and app connectivity is made standard on all trims. 

Driving It
Driving Impressions
Even the basic C250 sedan feels as solid and screwed together as the best S-Class. Stable and confident, the C-Class for 2013 is loaded with creature comforts and overflowing with technology. With the exception of the C63 AMG, the C-Class sedans and coupes tend to favor a ride that is more about comfort and quiet than tight turns and blistering acceleration. That's not to say that the rear-drive C-Class is slow or ponderous, far from it. Nimble in the corners and providing strong acceleration through the 7-speed automatic transmission, the C-Class is truly an enjoyable driving experience. Just don't expect it to perform like the BMW 3-Series. We found the C250's 1.8-liter turbocharged 4-cylinder a willing partner, but only when left in Sport mode. In the Comfort setting the power is only acceptable for a car of this cost and caliber. Models with the new 3.5-liter V6 are plenty potent even in Comfort mode.

Favorite Features
ATTENTION ASSIST 
This standard feature can detect when a driver is drowsy and alerts him or her via visual and audible warnings. How does it do that? The car uses sensors that "observe driver behavior," based primarily on steering wheel movements. 

MBRACE2 
A true leap forward in telematics, Mbrace2 is a Cloud-based subscription service that uses your smartphone to connect to the internet, allowing apps like Facebook, Google and Yelp to be online and at work whenever the car's in motion. Mbrace2 can even download system and map updates. 

Vehicle Details
Interior
The 2013 Mercedes-Benz C-Class is elegant yet relatively understated inside. A 4.5-inch color display sits before the driver relaying trip, audio and navigation information. Even when outfitted with the base M-B Tex vinyl upholstery, the C-Class seats are comfortable and supportive. Rear-seat space is a bit tight in the 5-passenger sedan, and even more cramped in the coupe, which seats four and has a lower roofline that can bump against heads. Like other luxury cars, audio, telephone and navigation are controlled via a console-mounted dial whose functions are viewed on a color-LCD screen in the center dash. 

Exterior
While most of the updates for the 2013 C-Class are under the hood and dashboard, Mercedes has made tweaks to the outer design of its smallest car. The biggest news is last year's introduction of a curvaceous coupe. Though it has two fewer doors than its sedan siblings, the C-Class coupe is nearly identical in length, width and wheelbase, but lower in height, giving it a more sporty appearance. C-Class Sedans retain their angular look and feature a lighter aluminum hood, revised front and rear bumpers and redesigned headlights and taillights. 

Notable Standard Equipment
All C-Class models come with a 7-speed automatic transmission, Attention Assist drowsiness monitor, 11 airbags, Mbrace2 telematics, a power sunroof, rain-sensing wipers, garage door opener, auto-dimming mirrors, dual-zone climate control, 8-way power front seats, 5.8-inch color screen with center controller and AM/FM/HD Radio with CD player and auxiliary/USB inputs. Coupes add a panorama roof, split-folding rear seats and paddle shifters for manual gear selection.

Notable Optional Equipment
Comfort, tech and safety options abound in the 2013 C-Class. Among them are an in-vehicle hotspot for internet connectivity, blind-spot monitor, rear-view camera, push-button start/stop, and a navigation system loaded with useful information such as ATM locations and Zagat Survey restaurant ratings. The high-end audio option is a 12-speaker, 450-watt harman/kardon Logic7 Surround Sound system. A new AMG Sports Package Plus adds enhanced exhaust tuning, sport interior, 18-inch 7-spoke wheels and, on coupes, a revised front suspension. 

Under the Hood
After a long absence, Mercedes is again using a 4-cylinder engine for its base model C-Class. The fuel-efficient 1.8-liter turbocharged 4-cylinder makes 201 horsepower, enabling the C250 to accelerate from zero to 60 mph in just 7.1 seconds. More powerful still is the C350, with a direct-injection 3.5-liter V6 that makes 302 horsepower (248 in the C300 4Matic). The incredible C63 AMG boasts a 6.3-liter V8 that makes 451 horsepower - and has fuel-economy numbers that add a one-time $1,700 gas-guzzler tax. All models now use a 7-speed automatic transmission with manual-shift mode (no manual transmission is available).

You'll Like This Car If...
As known quantities go, it doesn't get much better than a Camry. This 5-passenger family sedan builds on its reputation for reliability, safety, efficiency and easy driving manners. The Camry also recently benefited from an exterior update that injected style and youthfulness.

You May Not Like This Car If...
The Camry is very good at a lot of things, but it's not necessarily the best at any one. Toyota's midsize sedan isn't as fun to drive as a Mazda Mazda6 or even an Accord, nor is it as fuel-efficient as either. If you want all-wheel drive for improved traction, look to the Subaru Legacy or Ford Fusion.

What's New for 2017
Minor changes for the 2017 Camry include the addition of Toyota's Entune Audio Plus multimedia system with a navigation app and JBL Audio in XLE and XSE models, plus a standard Qi wireless phone charger for select smartphones.

Driving It
Driving Impressions
Thanks to revised suspension tuning that came with the 2015 revamp, the latest Camry sedan delivers a slightly livelier driving experience. But don't confuse the Camry for a corner-carver: Its emphasis remains quiet and comfortable road manners. The standard 178-horsepower 4-cylinder engine that most Camry buyers will choose is more than adequate for everyday acceleration and passing power. Linked exclusively to a 6-speed automatic transmission, it is a willing and faithful partner in the city, on country roads, or on interstate highways. Those who opt for the 268-horsepower V6 will be rewarded with surprisingly strong acceleration, a well of power reserves and only a slight reduction in fuel economy. The Camry XSE trim has a sportier flair, but its larger 18-inch wheels and stiffer shocks somewhat diminish ride quality. On the other end of the spectrum, the Camry Hybrid makes 40 mpg a reality with minimal loss of refinement.

Favorite Features
WIRELESS PHONE CHARGING
Tired of stringing wires across your console to charge your mobile devices? The 2017 Camry sedan eliminates this problem with the Qi-compatible wireless charging pad, now standard in XLE and XSE trims. Although most phones require a special case to take advantage of the pad, some newer phones already incorporate the technology.

SIMPLE CONTROLS
While other cars like the Honda Accord put an emphasis on touch-screen controls for audio and climate functions, the Camry sticks with knobs and buttons. They may look less digital, but in reality they are far easier to use, which we'll take any day.

Vehicle Details
Interior
The 5-passenger interior of the 2017 Camry isn't as stylistically forward as its exterior might suggest, but it's hardly bland. Moreover, it's supremely functional. Big cup holders and multiple storage nooks surround the sporty gear selector, and even the steering wheel has a familiar feel and looks more sophisticated now with its bevy of integrated controls. In the sportier SE and XSE models, paddle shifters bloom from the steering column for manually selecting gears. The Camry has good room for passengers up front and in back, and the trunk has a sizable 15.4 cubic feet of space. The trunk of Camry Hybrid models is a couple cubic feet smaller, but unlike the Honda Accord Hybrid, its rear seat folds. As mentioned above, the Camry uses traditional knobs and dials around its standard 6.1-inch or optional 7-inch display screen. The controls are big, easy to read and simple to use.

Exterior
Have you ever seen a more stylish Camry? We haven't. The significant revisions to the sheet metal that arrived a couple of years ago still look fresh for 2017. Bookended by an eye-catching front end and a nicely detailed rear, the stylish -- but not outlandish -- Camry is sure to attract new buyers without scaring away longtime devotees. For buyers who want extra edge, the Camry SE and XSE trims offer slightly more aggressive notes with piano-black lower front grille. Part of the beauty of the Camry Hybrid is that it looks similar to a standard model. You'll have to look pretty closely for that most fuel-efficient of Camrys, distinguished with subtle hybrid badges.

Notable Standard Equipment
The 2017 Camry sedan is available in four main versions: LE, SE, and two top trims, the XLE and XSE. The least-expensive Camry, the LE, includes an automatic transmission, backup camera, and 8-way power-adjustable driver's seat. Standard audio/infotainment includes a 6.1-inch touch screen and AM/FM/CD player with USB and auxiliary inputs, and Bluetooth phone connectivity with Siri Eyes Free compatibility for Apple products. The Camry's safety features include traction and stability controls, 10 airbags, and a battery-saver function that automatically shuts off interior lights if left on. The 2017 Camry also includes Toyota Care -- two years or 25,000 miles of scheduled maintenance and roadside assistance.

Notable Optional Equipment
Moving up to the SE model nets upgraded cloth seats, a leather-trimmed steering wheel, a sport-tuned suspension and 17-inch aluminum-alloy wheels, which we think is well worth the $770 bump over the base model. The Camry XLE and XSE include a leather interior with heated front seats, dual-zone climate control, a larger display screen with navigation and JBL audio, and the option of a V6. The XSE is the sportier of the pair with an Ultrasuede leather interior, shift paddles, a sport suspension, and 18-inch wheels. All models can be had with a moonroof. The XLE and XSE trims can be equipped with blind-spot monitoring, radar-based cruise control, lane-departure warning, and pre-collision braking. Unlike the Honda Accord, Apple CarPlay and Android Auto smartphone compatibility are not available on the 2017 Camry.

Title: salvage
Description:
This car is located in East Greenwich, Rhode Island. I am not interested in parting out the car. 

I spent a few years looking for a clean, unmodified, manual transmission second generation Mitsubishi Eclipse GSX. If you're familiar with these cars, they are almost always modified, so when a stock, well maintained example pops up, you have to jump on it. This one was fully optioned for the 1998 model year, so it has the Limited Slip Differential, CD Changer, Mud Flaps and Floor Mats.

I've owned the car for about 4 years, in that time I've continued to maintain the vehicle the way the previous owners had. Maintenance records from new are available for viewing. During my ownership the car has had it's timing belt and water pump replaced, new OEM wheel bearings on all four corners, new front brake calipers, and a new exhaust from the flex pipe back with a Magnaflow muffler. It was detailed and waxed approximately every six months.

Unfortunately, in April of 2017 while the car was parked on the street in front of my house, it was hit by a drunk driver who left the scene of the accident. At the time, I decided to explore the possibility of repairing the vehicle. The damages that occurred from the accident are as follows: frame damage in the engine bay, driver side headlight damage, driver side front suspension damage, damage to driver side front fender, damage to driver side door, paint damage to driver side of vehicle. While the vehicle was at the repair shop, the plan was also to repair the rot on the rocker panels, a very common issue on this generation of the Eclipse. It was during this undercarriage inspection that we came across a frame rail that had been previously repaired to a standard below my own, as well as some rot where one of the body mounts mount to the front subframe. These issues, along with the damage caused during the accident have just amounted to more than I'm interested in investing into this vehicle.

As the car sits today, it is partially disassembled. The driver side headlight is off, the tail lights are out, the front and rear bumper covers are off of the car. It still runs and is movable under its own power, but due to the front suspension damage, not truly drivable. It currently has 123,534 miles on it and will not go up for obvious reasons. The Air Conditioning is functional, and was recharged in 2015. All of the electronics work as normal, including the power antenna. The OEM radio is still installed. The front strut towers are solid.

As far as extra parts, there are quite a few. Everything to fix the damage from the accident, so headlight, fender, driver side door and suspension. An extra rim that is bent, but fixable. Two unmounted but used tires. I also have brand new OEM floor mats and a brand new OEM passenger side front fender.

While the car is fixable, it will make most sense for the majority of people to buy it as a parts car. If you are looking to AWD swap another Eclipse, everything that's needed is here. However, if you are able to do the bulk of the repairs yourself, then it may make sense to repair and keep the car. The car was declared a total loss, so if you intend to fix the car and drive it, it will need to be inspected by a state approved shop before it's road legal again.


I'm asking $2,900 or best reasonable offer. At that price you'll just be getting the car as it sits, plus the bumper covers and taillights. For $4,000 or best reasonable offer, you'll also get all of the spare parts, which alone are worth more than $1,500. Regardless of the accident damage, finding an unmodified, manual Eclipse GSX is liking pulling teeth. This ad is relatively thorough, but if you have any questions that I have not already answered or require additional photos, please do not hesitate to ask.

Description:
1971 LAND ROVER SERIES IIa: 

This not your average everyday Landy. Although it was built to look that way.  Through much effort and engineering one of the very first General Motors LTG 2.0 ltr. large bore, turbo-gas motors has been meticulously fitted into this special 88" land rover.  This repower brings the horses up to a trusty 272 HP with 295 FT-LBS torque.  Its married to a Tremec T56 6-speed manual transmission.  Which has been further coupled to a Forbyn Brothers / 2:1 Hi, 1:1 Lo transfer case.  The axles are Land Rover Salisbury Military - 4.11 Gears w/ Detroit TrueTrac.  All this new horsepower is brought to a stop with a Forbyn Brothers 4-Wheel Disc brake system.  Not your average driveline for 1971.  
The Landy was painted R-M Diamont single stage paint matching the Land Rover "Limestone" basecoat, with a matte clearcoat added for protection.  The client requested we preserve the "Original Patina" on the galvanized metal.  "Black Bridge" Custom Gauges finish off the modern gauge package.  Behind the dash we updated the creature comforts by adding a RestoMod "Bantam II" A/C, we also added heated & cooled front seats, and a hidden bespoke stereo.  There is both a hard top and brand-new soft-top that completes this special ride.  No expense was spared in building this one in a million Land Rover and its now going up for sale.  All of the above custom work was completed in-house at Black Bridge Motors Norwalk, CT  If you'd like to inspect the truck first hand we welcome your visit and with any questions please call

24 inch Scorpion Black Rims with Perrelli Scorpion AVR tires with less than 5,000 miles on them, plus additional 5th spare tire and 24 inch rim bolted into back interior cargo area. 

This Hummer is in great condition but does have some minor flaws. For instance, some of the dash and steering wheel buttons light bulbs are out, along with some of the bulbs in the floor board lighting that lights up the word HUMMER in blue when you open up any of the doors. These bulbs are very inexpensive and can be ordered on line or at any repair shop. There are some minor scrapes on the back bumper where the Matte Black has scratched off but no body or physical bumper damage.  Again these are minor flaws and can be seen in the pictures. Normal issues that come with custom adds, bells, whistles and such. 

Overall this vehicle is in great shape. It's performance is superior. The Super Charged V8 engine provides surprisingly fast acceleration for an SUV this size and you can feel added horsepower right away. This Hummer is truly a one of a kind vehicle that I hate to part with. You will not find anything like it anywhere and it no doubt stands alone in the Hummer H2 department. I rarely drive it and it's too bad ass to sit in the garage for 11 months out of the year. It's been well maintained and professionally serviced for the entire time I have owned it. Description:
So in the spirit of classic used car salesmanship, I will now do my best to convince you why your life will be (insert exaggerated number) percent better if you were to be rolling around in this road legal go-kart for grown ups. 

There are plenty of cars out there that you can immediately tell the type of person who's driving them (particularly giant lifted trucks (lol)). However, man or woman, young or old, Donald, Hillary or Bernie, this car somehow has no social demographic and everyone with a beating heart can have a good time driving it. If you're looking for something fun to get groceries in, you've found it. If you want something quick and nimble to get away from the cops in during your next bank heist, look no further (payment in non sequential bills if this is you). This little piece of English rally car history has a little something everyone can appreciate. From its' unique take on classic styling, to its' tight and responsive steering, it'll make even a devout nihilist believe they have found a purpose. 

Not convinced??? Well, how about some Pros and Cons???

Pros:

-Really low miles for the year
-Leather seats
-Well maintained and clean interior (it's my girlfriend's car, and she's meticulously, if not annoyingly clean)
-Push manual with paddle shifters (it has get-away car potential) 
-Fresh brake pads
-Mark Wahlberg, Jason Statham and Charlize Theron all looked awesome in the Italian Job remake (they also got away).
-It's a sporty, yet practical car that fits anyone (even Jason Statham)
-Great MPG

Cons:

-You cannot transport lumber 
-Not enough room to transport a family of 12 (possibly 10 with limited leg room)
-It unfortunately does not have an autopilot feature for casual car napping
-It beeps at you to change gears sometimes (actual con, I'll shift when I want to car)


If you're interested in this little mean machine, feel free to email me, or text me at (217) Forr Wan Sehhven Nine Phore Cix Cix. I picked this price because it is the average between the kelly blue book value for 'very good' and 'good'. That being said, it's my girlfriend's car and she has given me permission to be negotiable. So if you think you have a fair offer, worst I can do is say "how about this instead"

Title: clean
Description:
Well most pleasant greetings to you, casual craigslist car connoisseurs who's stumbled upon this post. Let me give you the quick reason why this car is so great, and no, it's not because of me. I got ridiculously lucky when I found this car on craigslist a couple years ago. The man I bought it from was the first and only owner, it had just shy of 100k on it, and this man took meticulous care of it. Meticulous to the point where the interior was, and is still in, suspiciously good shape (he may have been a warlock, I'm just guessing here). Meticulous to the point where he gave me, what seems to be, every single receipt for every single service checkup that was ever done to this fine piece of eastern machinery. So you'll inherit that lovely 20 year car biography neatly tucked away in the glove box upon purchasing. 

You may have also seen my recent post for my matte black 350z (because I guess I only need one four door now? For some unknown reason?), I'm bringing this up because I bought this car so I'd have a sporty and reliable car to drive around to save miles on my Z (and also because... more Japanese sports cars is always better). Ironically, I kinda fell in love with this car really fast, so I of course had to buy more cars to save miles on this car. This love also encouraged me to get this baby looking like the gorgeous Blasian super model you now see. Not saying she wasn't hot before she met me, but she's defiantly getting more looks now than ever. Styles change, and she was still wearing a coat from the 90s. So I methodically fixed all the little cosmetic issues that were keeping this long slender Asian princess from getting the respect she deserved, and then took her shopping to pick out a sleek 3m matte black dress to give her more of the 21st century sports car look she wanted so badly (treat your ladies gentleman, they deserve it). 

 Unfortunately, now, at the old and decrepit age of 23, it seems as though my ascension into adulthood has come with a collection of hefty prices. Prices that are clearing out my damn garage. But I've rambled enough. Here's the goods:

-DOHC VTEC - it still pumps power and ticks like clockwork
-Sport breaks - because the VTEC will obviously kill you otherwise
-Really well maintained interior - because of a possible warlock
-Blutooth and Phone connectivity - New Sony head unit to utilize the sound system, and hands free blah blah blah
-Bumping sound system - It's legitimately surprising how great the speakers are, 
-Sparco Shift Knob - I'm keeping the original shift knob to remember how great I had it once, everything else on the car is its' original part.
-Working everything - Please keep it that way if you buy it, it's a small miracle.

I'm fairly certain there is only one goofy problem with the car I could never figure out. The driver's side window controls only work when the door is open. It's like there's a wire that just doesn't quite connect when the door is shut, but when it's open, everything is absolutely fine. It's just a miniscule inconvenience at a drive through, but if popping the door before you order your big mac is your breaking point, then I guess I'm so sorry for wasting your time (that's me being facetious). 

Anywho, I'm Tony, and if you're interested in purchasing my Prelude to indirectly help me finance the payments to the financial institutions whom helped me finance my finance degree, then feel free to give me a text at (Too Wan Sehven) PhOOr Wun SeHVvan - NEIN fore CiXX CiXX. Or email me. But let's be honest here, you're not gonna email me. I priced it based on the other Preludes in the market and the KBB price. I'm friendly and negotiable, so respect me, and I'll respect you right on back.

Side note, I'd love to get my offer price, but if you offer exactly 4200 in cash, I will immediately accept with no negotiations... because it's hilarious.

Title: rebuilt
Description:
So I bought this bodacious Japanese harbinger of sexual arousal you're looking at when I lived in Miami 4 years ago. Although it had a rebuilt title and the man selling it to me spoke zero English, after inspecting it and driving it I realized apparently "rebuilt" in Spanish also means "bargain", so I bought it on the spot. There are three things you learn to love behind the wheel of this mobile defibrillator: the sound of your own car, how slow 80mph can feel, and the ego boost you get when people break their neck trying to get a double take. Now, I can't promise you that everyone will love it, but I can promise that they will look at it anyway. 

You're probably wondering why I would sell something that can literally get you laid by waving at a beautiful blonde girl you're passing on the highway (yes, that actually happened, I couldn't believe it either, coolest moment of my life). Well in short, it's impossible to steer this car past my throbbing car inspired erection.... Just kidding, I graduated college and I'm apparently supposed to be "responsible" now and "grow up and actually use my 2 business degrees" or some bs like that. Side note, I also moved in with my girlfriend, completely unrelated to that last sentence.... he said sarcastically... 

Anywho, here's what you actually want to know. The goods:

-Upgraded Exhaust (done in Miami, it sounds amazing, it's also the reason the check engine light wont go off fyi)
-Sport front Calipers and Rotors (if you go fast, ya gotta stop fast too)
-Sport Clutch (cuz, duh)
-Sony touch screen head unit (it's got blutooth, usb and aux, it's also sub ready)
-Brand new set of Drift Z Rims and Tires (they both have like 20 miles on them total, you can't have my Lexani rims, sorry)
-Sparco Shift Knob (Literally bought this because I want to keep the old stock knob as a memento, your lucky day)
-Custom front and back bumper (don't hit anything, they were a lot of work to get right dammit)
-Matte Black 3m 1080 M12 car vinyl wrap (because seriously, how awesome does that shit look?)
----The only thing I think is really wrong with the car is a dent in the passenger side door that some asshole left for me. 

I tried to make sure the things I did to the car would make it more awesome, not ricey. I hate ricers, so I hope that you see this as a tasteful, yet maniacally badass car monstrosity. Since I know this will come up, all jokes aside, yes it's a certified rebuilt, I bought it that way in Miami. That being said, rebuilt doesn't mean you get to haggle with me like we're at a Tijuana bracelet stand.  

If you want it, and promise me eye to eye you will take good care of it, I will regretfully barter the car to you in exchange for green rectangles or a certified bank rectangle. 

I'm Tony, number is (ToO-Won-SehVen) PhouR-Wan-Sleven NEIN-Foore-Sixx-Syx. 
If you can read that, feel free to text me, or I check my emails.

***Update - Yes, I'm totally negotiable. The price on the ad is a strategic, yet arbitrarily random number. It isn't firm... Unless you want to pay that number... In which case I will totally take that number.... but only if you insist...
***Update #2 - Unfortunately, I don't want to trade. It's not that I don't like motorcycles, boats, jetskis, lifted trucks, Apache attack choppers and or other asian sports cars. It's just I have too many vehicles as it is, not enough room for them all, and not enough legs and arms to drive them all... that and student loans.... lots of student loans.... soul crippling, car stealing, downright depressing, no default policy having, future economic collapse causing, government organized thievery. And Uncle Sam wants his mother f#$%ing money yesterday.

Title: clean
Description:
If you are looking for an affordable, reliable vehicle for your leisure, you'd best look elsewhere because this Maxima will come with no such attributes! If you're an up-and-coming mechanic and would like to dabble, this might be for you, though...

As it currently is, this Maxima requires new fron brake pads and rotors, a front brake caliper, and left and right front brake hose replacements--- all of which I'm unwilling to learn to do myself and am absolutely not paying the amount quoted by the mechanic of just a few bucks short of $700.

As well, it has a white paint job with decadent streaks of brown rust which adds jacks**t to its aesthetics. For the incense-lovers out there, the trunk has the slight odor of milk thanks to the roommates of a friend who once had loosely-capped containers of milk in the back that spilled over, (who didn't even have the courtesy to apologize after realizing this, by the way). 

If these are insufficient in offending your senses still, I'd like to take you to the interior which is also not a pleaser for the eyes! Due to a lineage of negligent vehicle owners (including myself, of course), the floors are mucked up and covered with bits of rock and dead leaves, you'd think you were stepping into a state park when you get into this thing for a ride.

On a more serious note, though this car (like myself as a car-owner) is not without its faults, it's gotten me from Chicago to Champaign or vice versa about 15 times in the almost two years I've had it, as well as from campus to the stores on Prospect Ave even more so. It'll definitely get you from A to B, just not every time. I think the highest mileage I had with this car without incident (i.e. something breaking down or in need or repair) was about 1,500 miles. But all I did with the car ws fill the gas, have the oil changed, and refill the under-the-hood fluids when it deserves more care and maintenance, probably.


------------------------------------------


[TL;DR] 

- Needs some brake replacements and repairs. Can't get myself to fix these issues, and after having to deal with many repairs over the course of almost two years of ownership, I'd rather just sell it to someone willing to take care of it. Once the brakes are dealt with, the car will drive well. Otherwise, I'd recommend towing the car, else you'd have to force the car to drive with the brakes clamped down.

-Trunk smells of milk

- The AC works, though it is more refrigerator-cold than freezer-cold.

- The rear left door won't open. Will have to replace the inner locking mechanisms to fix that, which apparently costs a bit in the $300s according to my mechanic.

- Lots of rust on the side skirts and around the rear wheels

- A few dings, scrapes, dents, and a damaged rear-right bumper

- Unappealing, dirty interior floor

- No audio jack to directly connect a phone or audio device, only CD's and cassette tapes. An iClever mini universal FM transmitter will be provided, though it won't suffice if static is a real pain for you

- Took it in to the shop to have the wheels repaired since they were leaking air bad a couple months ago, but the front left still seems to be sagging after having air pumped to 35 psi like the rest of the tires, so that might be an issue after the brakes are done.


If you're interested or if you have any inquiries, do let me know!
*** Only accepting cash

- Big kitchen with so much coutnertop space! If you love to cook this is a MUST. There is a propane tank in the back to power a camping stove that is included. 
- A dometic fridge is included that is powered by solar. 
- A second cooler is included that I use to store dry foods. 
-15 gallon fresh water tank and 5 gallon dark water tank all powered by a foot pump. I love the foot pump!
- Plenty of storage underneath back kitchen countertops and above the driver/passenger seat in the bulk heads. 

I've used this van for stealth urban camping and for extended camping at national parks as well. Its great for both! 

I am willing to drive the van anywhere in the country to deliver or for someone to inspect, but there will be a nonrefundable deposit required depending on the distance I have to travel. Van is currently in central Illinois.

Please email or text with any questions!

Title: clean
Description:
$2000 firm need gone asap!


This post is very hard for me to type. I bought this truck nearly 2 years ago to restore. It was and still is in need of help. I bought it from a guy who didn't take care of it and sat for 2 and a half year's. 

I bought it and did extensive work and put ALOT of money into it while it sat at a friend's house. I drove it home the oem exhaust piping fell off from the manifold while taking it on a short cruise that day. Parked it and started going to town on it. I did pace setter long tubes, accel ceramic plugs,ac Delco plugs,new cap and rotor,accel coil,new cam and crank sensor. Can't get any pulse to fire... might be out of timing. I put wayyy too much money I will NEVER get back out of it. I just need it out of my driveway.. sadly I lost interest in it.

I have well over 4k just in additional parts in it just as it sits. Here is a list of things I have done to it so far.

Put a motor in it from a 97 Tahoe with 112k miles.
All moog suspension parts.
New upper control arms,bushings, inner and outer tie rod ends,sway bar links. Leveling keys,helper springs,3"rear blocks.
Swapped a rear end.
New brakes,turned rotors.
E fans
Skyjacker shocks
Pace setter long tube headers
Accel ceramic plug wires
A.c. Delco plugs
Accel coil. Ok I'm forgetting alot at this moment but just get a Hold of me if interested. I will go threw literally everything with you.

It's sitting on 22" rims right now, tires good. I painted 2 of the rims black the other 2 need sanded down and finished. I have factory rims also. It also has 1"rear hub centric spacers in the rear and .75" in the front. New led tails..blacked out fronts.. needs a new front bumper and hood(hood has rust) 

It's a 1999 original Denali w 230k miles so it's go it's flaws. Previous owner said trans was rebuilt at 150k. It is a solid truck, I just found something else I'd rather have. Price is firm. So please don't waste my time.. I'm telling you it has it's flaws but if someone would finish it it would be a solid nice truck.

Has front dif drop installed for the added lift. I honestly can keep going on and on about the truck but I'm going to leave this info to someone actually interested in it. 

Idc if you buy it for parts. Just please don't waste my time.

Edit: I pulled the factory intake to carb it. But something serious has came up and I just need it out of my driveway.. .first person to bring me $2000 and a trailer gets it. Will not hold!!!
